description: Install command help
---
Installs the project dependencies from the composer.lock file if present, or falls back on the
composer.json

Usage: libretto install [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --no-dev
          Skip dev dependencies

  -q, --quiet
          Do not output any message

      --ansi
          Force ANSI output (colors and formatting)

      --prefer-dist
          Prefer dist packages (archives)

      --no-ansi
          Disable ANSI output (colors and formatting)

      --prefer-source
          Prefer source packages (VCS)

      --dry-run
          Dry run (don't install anything)

  -n, --no-interaction
          Do not ask any interactive question

      --ignore-platform-reqs
          Ignore platform requirements

      --profile
          Display timing and memory usage information

      --ignore-platform-req <REQ>
          Ignore specific platform requirements (e.g., php, ext-*)

      --no-plugins
          Disables all plugins

  -o, --optimize-autoloader
          Optimize autoloader

  -a, --classmap-authoritative
          Generate classmap for PSR-0/4 autoloading

  -d, --working-dir <DIR>
          Use the specified directory as working directory

      --apcu-autoloader
          `APCu` autoloader caching

      --no-cache
          Prevent use of the cache

      --format <FORMAT>
          Output format (text, json, or table)

          Possible values:
          - table: Human-readable table format
          - json:  JSON format
          - text:  Plain text format
          
          [default: text]

      --no-scripts
          Skip scripts execution

      --prefer-lowest
          Prefer lowest versions (for testing)

  -v, --verbose...
          Increase the verbosity of messages: -v for verbose, -vv for very verbose, -vvv for debug

      --prefer-stable
          Prefer stable versions

      --minimum-stability <STABILITY>
          Minimum stability (dev, alpha, beta, RC, stable)

      --no-progress
          Disable progress bar

      --concurrency <CONCURRENCY>
          Maximum concurrent HTTP requests
          
          [default: 64]

      --audit
          Run security audit after installation

      --fail-on-audit
          Fail installation if security vulnerabilities are found

      --verify-checksums
          Verify package checksums and fail on mismatch

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
